  "evidence_excerpts": [
    {
      "text": "Needs Review\n147\na higher kind of life, initiation into divinity, into the company of the gods; by eating the flesh and drinking the blood of the god who sacrified himself for men by dying, men acquire some of his divinity, hence eternal life. Jesus says this explicitly, so this isn’t just an inference on my part based on comparing the Eucharist with the sacraments of other religions.\n\nIt seems to me that I first came across this idea in a book by Joseph Campbell; he said something like, \"Christ",
      "matched_alias": "Joseph Campbell",
      "term_id": "TERM_joseph-campbell",
      "term_name": "Joseph Campbell",
      "term_slug": "joseph-campbell"
    }
  ],
